TITLE: Defining Koin Framework Characteristics
DESCRIPTION: A concise description of Koin's core features, highlighting it as a DSL (Domain Specific Language), a lightweight container, and having a pragmatic API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/introduction.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
Koin is a DSL, a light container and a pragmatic API
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Declaring a Koin Module in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to declare a basic Koin module using the 'module' function. This is the fundamental way to group related dependency definitions in Koin.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/modules.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
val myModule = module {
    // Your definitions ...
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Starting Koin with Module Configuration in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to start a Koin container with modules using the startKoin function. It initializes a KoinApplication instance in the GlobalContext, configures logging, and declares the modules to be used.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/dsl.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
// start a KoinApplication in Global context
startKoin {
    // declare used logger
    logger()
    // declare used modules
    modules(coffeeAppModule)
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Injecting Dependencies in Android Activity using Koin
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to inject a UserPresenter into an Android Activity using Koin's by inject() delegate function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/quickstart/android.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class MainActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

    private val presenter: UserPresenter by inject()

    override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)

        //...
    }
}
```

