TITLE: Creating a Basic Koin Module in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a basic Koin module that serves as a container for dependency definitions. The module function creates a space where dependencies can be declared for injection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/dsl.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
val myModule = module {
   // your dependencies here
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Initializing Koin in a Kotlin Application
DESCRIPTION: Basic example showing how to initialize Koin in a Kotlin application's main function. This is the starting point for using Koin dependency injection in any Kotlin project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/setup/koin.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
    startKoin {
        modules(...)
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Starting Koin in Android Application Class
DESCRIPTION: Initialization of Koin in the Application class's onCreate method, setting up the Android context, logger, and loading the application module for dependency injection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/quickstart/android-viewmodel.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class MainApplication : Application(){
    override fun onCreate() {
        super.onCreate()

        startKoin{
            androidLogger()
            androidContext(this@MainApplication)
            modules(appModule)
        }
    }
}
```

