TITLE: Using Module Includes in Koin 3.2+
DESCRIPTION: Introduces the 'includes' function for composing Koin modules. This feature allows for better organization of modules, especially in modularized projects, by including child modules within a parent module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/modules.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
// `:feature` module
val childModule1 = module {
    /* Other definitions here. */
}
val childModule2 = module {
    /* Other definitions here. */
}
val parentModule = module {
    includes(childModule1, childModule2)
}

// `:app` module
startKoin { modules(parentModule) }
```

