TITLE: Using Shared ViewModels in Activity and Fragments in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the same ViewModel instance across an Activity and its Fragments using activityViewModel() function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-android/viewmodel.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class WeatherActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

    /*
     * Declare WeatherViewModel with Koin and allow constructor dependency injection
     */
    private val weatherViewModel by viewModel<WeatherViewModel>()
}

class WeatherHeaderFragment : Fragment() {

    /*
     * Declare shared WeatherViewModel with WeatherActivity
     */
    private val weatherViewModel by activityViewModel<WeatherViewModel>()
}

class WeatherListFragment : Fragment() {

    /*
     * Declare shared WeatherViewModel with WeatherActivity
     */
    private val weatherViewModel by activityViewModel<WeatherViewModel>()
}
```

