TITLE: Implementing Module Linking Strategies in Koin
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use modules to implement different strategy implementations, such as different datasource implementations for a repository. This showcases Koin's flexibility in managing dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/modules.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class Repository(val datasource : Datasource)
interface Datasource
class LocalDatasource() : Datasource
class RemoteDatasource() : Datasource

val repositoryModule = module {
    single { Repository(get()) }
}

val localDatasourceModule = module {
    single<Datasource> { LocalDatasource() }
}

val remoteDatasourceModule = module {
    single<Datasource> { RemoteDatasource() }
}

// Load Repository + Local Datasource definitions
startKoin {
    modules(repositoryModule,localDatasourceModule)
}

// Load Repository + Remote Datasource definitions
startKoin {
    modules(repositoryModule,remoteDatasourceModule)
}
```

