TITLE: Using withOptions for Module Definition Configuration in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the withOptions operator introduced in Koin 3.2 that allows specifying additional configuration options for dependency definitions, such as qualifiers, binding interfaces, and creation timing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/insertkoinio/koin/blob/main/docs/reference/koin-core/dsl.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
module {
    single { ClassA(get()) } withOptions { 
        named("qualifier")
        createdAtStart()
    }
}
```

